{"questionId":"12175","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question investigates the sum of sine and cosine functions</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The expression&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + 4\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x\">\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> can be written in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A\\,{\\text{cos}}(Bx + C) + D\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A{\\text{,}}\\,\\,B \\in {\\mathbb{R}^ + }\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C{\\text{,}}\\,\\,D \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\pi&nbsp; < C \\leqslant \\pi \">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The expression&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + 12\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x\">\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>12</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> can&nbsp;be written in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A\\,{\\text{cos}}(Bx + C) + D\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A{\\text{,}}\\,\\,B \\in {\\mathbb{R}^ + }\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C{\\text{,}}\\,\\,D \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\pi&nbsp; < C \\leqslant \\pi \">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>By considering the graph of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 5\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + 12\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>12</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>, find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"B\">\n  <mi>B</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C\">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"D\">\n  <mi>D</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/dd8245b3b4c2add3580f5f0593847b597521e6c7.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = 13\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>13</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"B = 1\">\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"D = 0\">\n  <mi>D</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>maximum at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 0.395\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.395</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>So C =&nbsp;−0.395&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( { =&nbsp; - {\\text{arctan}}\\frac{5}{{12}}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>arctan</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>5</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>12</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12175","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.5d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By considering the graph of y = 5 sin x + 12 cos x , find the value of A , B , C and D .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.7—Circular functions: graphs, composites, transformations","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Compound angle identities"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}